The paper deals with citation matching, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR) and digital libraries (DL). It also involves indexing and processing large amounts of data, which are typical concerns in database (DB) and cyberinfrastructure (CY) research. Additionally, the use of MapReduce and Hadoop suggests a focus on distributed computing, which is relevant to the computer networks and distributed systems (CR) sub-category.
